    "body": "Even though the feature sounds useful to me, I have some doubts how this could be actually implemented. These doubts boil down to me not understanding the difference between validators/accounts and how they are exactly related to key files.\r\n\r\nFor example, if there are two pairs of key files in one directory, how can the user specify which pair they want to encrypt using a different password? Should the user provide the name of any one of the files from a pair? Or maybe some kind of an account/validator ID?\r\n\r\nI mentioned my lack of knowledge on Discord: https://discordapp.com/channels/476244492043812875/667763844365680650/710607681949401119",
